value.value: The anatomical space that is encircled by the lateral bar of the mesoscutellum.
The corner at the intersection of the ventrolateral and posterior margin of the metapleuron.
The line of separation between the pronotum and the mesoscutum.
The line of separation between the pronotum and the mesopectus.
The straight line that extends ventrally on the lateral (vertical) surface of the mesopectus and is oriented anteroposteriorly.
The area of the metapectal-propodeal complex that is anterior to the metapleural carina and lateral to the metadiscrimen.
The sensillum with a hair-like cuticular component.
The trichoid sensillum that is apically rounded.
The seta that is located laterally on the clypeus.
The sensillum with a distal, volcano-shape cuticular component on the apical-most flagellomere.
The row of sensilla whose cuticular component are flat, circular and lack a median peg.
The sensillum coeloconicum, in which the diameter of the tip of the hairlike cuticular component is 1/3-1/5 of the diameter of the surrounding depression.
The sensillum coeloconicum, in which the diameter of the tip of the hairlike cuticular component is as wide as the surrounding depression.
The anatomical cluster composed of the transaxillar carina, axillar carina, and axillular carina.
The segment that is metameric along the proximal-distal axis and is part of an appendage.

The anatomical line that connects the global minima of the contour line of the pronotal slope in lateral view when the specimen is rotated until the contour line becames as symmetric as possible and the posteriormost point of the propodeal lobe.
The median anatomical line between the setal line of petiole and the transverse carina of petiole.
The anteriormost setal pit on the dorsal side of the petiole.
The scrobe that is dorsal to the propodeal foramen and accommodates the proximodorsal area of the petiole.
The anatomical line between the intersections of the cranium contour and dorsal head line in frontal view.
The anatomical line between the posteriormost (dorsalmost) points of compound eyes in frontal view.
The anatomical line that is perpendicular to the median anatomical line and is the tangent at the distalmost point(s) of the clypeus in frontal view.

The anatomical line that extends between the distalmost point of the subpetiolar process and the global minima of the contour line of the dorsal region of the posterior petiolar constriction in lateral view when the specimen is rotated until the contour line became as symmetric as possible.
The petiolar area posterior to the posterior petiolar constriction.
The anatomical line between the distal ends of the propodeal spines.
The area of the scape that faces away from the cranial surface in fully caudal scape position.
The area of the scape that faces the cranium surface when the scape is in fully flexed position.
The anatomical line that is tangential to the posteriormost points of the antennal rims.
The transverse torular line that extends between the frontal carinae.
The carina that extends between the ventral (anterior) margin of the antennal foramen to the apical clypeal margin.
The median anatomical line that extends between the posterior margin of the cranium and the distal clypeal line in frontal view.
The anatomical line that is the longest between the dorsal margin of the petiole and the posterior petiolar distance and perpendicular to the posterior petiolar distance.
The anatomical line that is the longest between the ventral margin of the petiole and the dorsal margin of the petiole and is perpendicular to the ventral margin of the petiole in lateral view.

label.value: maximum cephalic length in median line

value.value: The median anatomical line that extends between the posterior margin of the cranium and the distal margin of the clypeus in frontal view.
The median notch that is on the distal clypeal margin.
The anatomical line that is between the distal clypeal line and the proximalmost point of the distal clypeal notch in frontal view.
The anatomical line that connects the center of the propodeal spiracle with the posteriormost point of the propodeal lobe in lateral view.
The longest width of the pronotum in dorsal view.
The anatomical line that is the shortest between the center of the petiolar spiracle and the posterior margin of the petiole in lateral view.

label.value: anterodorsal spine of the petiolar node

value.value: The anterolateral spine of the dorsal side of the petiolar node.
The anatomical line between the distal ends of the anterodorsal spines of the petiolar node.
The maximum width of the petiole in dorsal view.
The median anatomical line of the cranium that is the longest between the dorsal margin of the cranium and the dorsal head width.
The longest anatomical line that is perpendicular to the posterior margin of the postpetiole in lateral view and is between the posterior postpetiolar margin and the anterior postpetiolar margin.
The maximum width of the postpetiole in dorsal view.
The scrobe on the pronotum that accommodates the posterior surface of the cranium.
The spine that is located at the dorsolateral edge of the cranial scrobe of the pronotum.
The anatomical line between the distal ends of the pronotal spines.
The proximodistal anatomical line of the scapal area that is distal to the radicle.
The anatomical line between the center of the propodeal spiracle and the distal end of the propodeal spine.
